---
// Two ICs sharing a long GND return. When IC A switches, V = L di/dt
// appears across the return inductance → IC B sees a lifted local ground.
---
<figure class="not-prose rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4">
  <svg viewBox="0 0 480 220" class="w-full" role="img" aria-label="Ground bounce — shared return inductance">
    <rect x="1" y="1" width="478" height="218" fill="#fff" stroke="#e2e8f0" />
    <text x="10" y="18" font-size="11" font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="#0f172a">GROUND BOUNCE — shared return L</text>

    <!-- IC A (noisy switcher) -->
    <rect x="30"  y="40" width="70" height="60" fill="#0f172a" />
    <text x="48"  y="74" font-size="11" fill="#fff" font-family="ui-monospace, monospace">IC A</text>
    <text x="40"  y="88" font-size="8"  fill="#fbbf24" font-family="ui-monospace, monospace">big di/dt</text>

    <!-- IC B (victim) -->
    <rect x="380" y="40" width="70" height="60" fill="#0f172a" />
    <text x="398" y="74" font-size="11" fill="#fff" font-family="ui-monospace, monospace">IC B</text>
    <text x="390" y="88" font-size="8"  fill="#60a5fa" font-family="ui-monospace, monospace">victim</text>

    <!-- shared GND return trace (long/thin) -->
    <line x1="65" y1="100" x2="65" y2="150"  stroke="#94a3b8" stroke-width="2" />
    <line x1="65" y1="150" x2="415" y2="150" stroke="#94a3b8" stroke-width="2" />
    <line x1="415" y1="150" x2="415" y2="100" stroke="#94a3b8" stroke-width="2" />
    <!-- inductor symbol in the middle -->
    <path d="M 210 150 q 6 -10 12 0 q 6 -10 12 0 q 6 -10 12 0 q 6 -10 12 0 q 6 -10 12 0"
          fill="none" stroke="#94a3b8" stroke-width="2" />
    <text x="218" y="172" font-size="10" fill="#64748b" font-family="ui-monospace, monospace">L_return</text>

    <!-- di/dt arrow from IC A -->
    <path d="M 65 105 Q 65 125 80 125" fill="none" stroke="#fbbf24" stroke-width="1.5" />
    <polygon points="76,121 84,125 76,129" fill="#fbbf24" />
    <text x="90" y="120" font-size="9" fill="#a16207" font-family="ui-monospace, monospace">i(t)</text>

    <!-- voltage drop annotation — split across two lines so it fits the viewBox on narrow viewports -->
    <g font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" text-anchor="middle" fill="#b91c1c">
      <text x="240" y="188" font-size="10" font-weight="600">V_bounce = L · di/dt</text>
      <text x="240" y="202" font-size="9">수 ns 에 수백 mA 가 바뀌면 수십–수백 mV</text>
    </g>

    <!-- IC B sees lifted ground -->
    <g>
      <line x1="425" y1="110" x2="465" y2="110" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="3 2" />
      <text x="440" y="128" font-size="9" fill="#1d4ed8" font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" text-anchor="middle">local GND</text>
      <text x="440" y="140" font-size="9" fill="#1d4ed8" font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" text-anchor="middle">↑ 흔들림</text>
    </g>
  </svg>
  <figcaption class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
    IC A 의 switching 전류가 공유 return 인덕턴스를 지나가면 양단에 <span class="text-rose-600 font-semibold">V = L·di/dt</span> 만큼
    전압이 생기고, 이게 IC B 의 기준(ground) 을 밀어올립니다. 결과 — IC B 의 로직 임계가 흔들려 false 트리거·리셋·데이터 에러.
  </figcaption>
</figure>
